description: The prime minister has started consultations with political parties and labor unions. While an agreement between the centrist bloc and the right is possible, the Socialists are still hesitant to compromise.

description: The spokesperson for Qatar's foreign ministry told Le Monde that the Gulf emirate is considering legal action against Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, whom he describes as a 'thug' and 'unhinged.'

headline: In devastated Kathmandu, young Nepalese fear old leaders' return
description: No seat of power was spared in Nepal's capital during two days of unprecedented protest. The army, which has seized control of the country, is negotiating a way out of the crisis after the prime minister resigned and the president disappeared. Yet the young people behind the movement have little say in what comes next.
